- [liquor sloshes]

1294
00:51:13,250 --> 00:51:15,458
[grunts]

1295
00:51:15,541 --> 00:51:18,125
All right. Then I'll use
the last little bit

1296
00:51:18,208 --> 00:51:20,000
of my extra mana
to share this snow

1297
00:51:20,083 --> 00:51:22,791
with all the people
who are living in the capital!

1298
00:51:24,333 --> 00:51:26,041
[music playing]

1299
00:52:12,875 --> 00:52:14,416
[door closes]

1300
00:52:14,500 --> 00:52:15,791
- My, what's this?

1301
00:52:16,791 --> 00:52:17,750
So have you finally had enough

1302
00:52:17,833 --> 00:52:20,791
of your little tryst
with Subaru?

1303
00:52:20,875 --> 00:52:22,791
- You shouldn't tease anybody
in that outfit.

1304
00:52:22,875 --> 00:52:26,375
I don't find it funny
in the least.

1305
00:52:26,458 --> 00:52:28,583
- Goodness!
You can't be honest, can you?

1306
00:52:28,666 --> 00:52:32,000
[ice cubes clatter]

1307
00:52:32,625 --> 00:52:35,291
This is for you.

1308
00:52:35,375 --> 00:52:37,708
Not having a single drop
on a fanciful night

1309
00:52:37,791 --> 00:52:40,000
such as this
would be such a crime.

1310
00:52:40,958 --> 00:52:42,583
- I'll pass, I suppose.

1311
00:52:42,666 --> 00:52:44,041
- Staying faithful to him,
is that it?

1312
00:52:44,125 --> 00:52:48,208
- Now, don't get
the wrong idea about this.

1313
00:52:48,291 --> 00:52:49,666
My choice to not drink

1314
00:52:49,750 --> 00:52:53,666
has nothing to do with
that boy's request, I suppose.

1315
00:52:53,750 --> 00:52:57,250
Long ago, my mother
discouraged me from doing so,

1316
00:52:57,333 --> 00:52:58,375
and that's all.

1317
00:52:59,958 --> 00:53:01,958
[no audible dialogue]

1318
00:53:02,041 --> 00:53:05,708
What he says has nothing
to do with me, I suppose.

1319
00:53:05,791 --> 00:53:07,875
[no audible dialogue]

1320
00:53:27,666 --> 00:53:30,291
[birds chirping]

1321
00:53:30,375 --> 00:53:31,750
- I was just thinking...

1322
00:53:31,833 --> 00:53:32,750
maybe we should have asked
for Subaru's help

1323
00:53:32,833 --> 00:53:34,041
from the very beginning.

1324
00:53:34,125 --> 00:53:36,125
That way, neither one of us
would have felt

1325
00:53:36,208 --> 00:53:39,333
quite so anxious
about what was happening here.

1326
00:53:39,416 --> 00:53:40,666
- Yeah, you got a point.

1327
00:53:40,750 --> 00:53:42,291
But then again,
it wouldn't be good

1328
00:53:42,375 --> 00:53:43,916
if you grew up to be
somebody who's always

1329
00:53:44,000 --> 00:53:45,958
relying on other people
for everything, either,

1330
00:53:46,041 --> 00:53:47,791
so even if things seem
way beyond your control,

1331
00:53:47,875 --> 00:53:49,583
give it a try first, okay?

1332
00:53:49,666 --> 00:53:52,041
- Yes, I understand.

1333
00:53:52,125 --> 00:53:52,583
- Good to hear.

1334
00:53:52,666 --> 00:53:54,958
[both laugh]

1335
00:53:55,041 --> 00:53:56,541
EMILIA: Hey, do you remember

1336
00:53:56,625 --> 00:53:58,875
what Subaru suggested
during his toast?

1337
00:53:58,958 --> 00:54:01,541
- Hmm. That we should hold
another snow festival

1338
00:54:01,625 --> 00:54:04,000
during next year's
magic release period?

1339
00:54:04,083 --> 00:54:06,375
Normally, I wouldn't assume
he'd be interested,

1340
00:54:06,458 --> 00:54:07,458
but I have a feeling

1341
00:54:07,541 --> 00:54:09,791
he could make the next one
even more lively.

1342
00:54:09,875 --> 00:54:10,583
- Me, too.

1343
00:54:10,666 --> 00:54:13,458
I think that side
of him is just so...

1344
00:54:13,541 --> 00:54:15,000
you know.

1345
00:54:15,083 --> 00:54:16,416
- Indeed, it is.

1346
00:54:16,500 --> 00:54:18,958
I think it's extremely
"you know" as well.

1347
00:54:19,041 --> 00:54:20,541
- Next year, huh?

1348
00:54:20,625 --> 00:54:23,958
I'm not sure what'll happen
that far into the future.

1349
00:54:24,041 --> 00:54:25,500
I wonder how it'll be.

1350
00:54:25,583 --> 00:54:26,833
- At this point,
it's pretty hard to say,

1351
00:54:26,916 --> 00:54:28,958
but I hope things turn out

1352
00:54:29,041 --> 00:54:30,750
exactly how you
want them to, Lia,

1353
00:54:30,833 --> 00:54:32,583
even if there's no guarantee

1354
00:54:32,666 --> 00:54:34,500
that the snow festival
he was talking about

1355
00:54:34,583 --> 00:54:36,000
will actually take place.

1356
00:54:36,083 --> 00:54:37,958
- You're not
against the idea now, are you?

1357
00:54:38,041 --> 00:54:39,833
- No, it's not that at all.

1358
00:54:39,916 --> 00:54:42,500
I had a whole lot of fun,

1359
00:54:42,583 --> 00:54:45,083
and it looked to me
like you did, too.

1360
00:54:45,166 --> 00:54:47,750
But I'm just wondering
if Subaru will still be happy

1361
00:54:47,833 --> 00:54:50,541
staying by your side
until next year rolls around.

1362
00:54:51,916 --> 00:54:53,708
The wounds on his belly,

1363
00:54:53,791 --> 00:54:55,375
the one from the witch
biting him,

1364
00:54:55,458 --> 00:54:56,708
all of those scars
he's gotten,

1365
00:54:56,791 --> 00:54:59,958
are the indirect results
of your actions.

1366
00:55:00,041 --> 00:55:02,291
It's not as if
you would ever forget that,

1367
00:55:02,375 --> 00:55:03,500
but it's still
important to remember.

1368
00:55:04,541 --> 00:55:06,500
- [sighs]

1369
00:55:06,583 --> 00:55:07,875
- I really hope we can have

1370
00:55:07,958 --> 00:55:09,041
another snow festival
next year, though,

1371
00:55:09,125 --> 00:55:11,166
because having
the excess mana to do it again

1372
00:55:11,250 --> 00:55:12,875
would mean
I didn't have to use it

1373
00:55:12,958 --> 00:55:15,416
on anything big before that.

1374
00:55:15,500 --> 00:55:17,500
And I can't think
of anyone but Subaru

1375
00:55:17,583 --> 00:55:18,500
who could lead
an entire festival.

1376
00:55:20,541 --> 00:55:23,083
- Right. That is true.

1377
00:55:23,166 --> 00:55:25,041
Uh-huh.

1378
00:55:25,125 --> 00:55:27,708
I'm hoping that happens again
as well, Puck.

1379
00:55:29,041 --> 00:55:30,125
Uh, is something wrong?

1380
00:55:30,208 --> 00:55:31,166
- [gasps]

1381
00:55:32,166 --> 00:55:32,708
Mm-mmm. No, not at all.

1382
00:55:32,791 --> 00:55:34,708
I'm just fine!

1383
00:55:34,791 --> 00:55:37,500
Looks like it'll be hot today,
so take care.

1384
00:55:37,583 --> 00:55:37,875
- [chuckles]
- Will do.

1385
00:55:37,958 --> 00:55:38,750
See you later!

1386
00:55:38,833 --> 00:55:41,541
[music playing]

1387
00:55:47,875 --> 00:55:49,833
- [groaning]

1388
00:55:51,166 --> 00:55:52,083
[gasps]

1389
